LOS ANGELES (KABC) -- It will be a pleasant and warm weekend across Southern California, with highs in the 70s and 80s.

Marine layer clouds will hang around Los Angeles and Orange counties, as well as the valleys and Inland Empire, keeping skies partly sunny. Temperatures will hover in the low 80s.

Beaches will also see morning clouds and later partly sunny skies, with highs in the low 80s.

Mountains will experience a sunny, cool day with highs in the upper 60s.

Deserts will be sunny and breezy in the afternoons as temperatures reach the mid-80s.
